\title{Lead Research Assistant}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Identifies high-quality leads for your product or service by analyzing}

\subtree{
\title{Lead Research Assistant}
\p{This skill helps you identify and qualify potential leads for your business by analyzing your product/service, understanding your ideal customer profile, and providing actionable outreach strategies.}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\ul{
\li{Finding potential customers or clients for your product/service}
\li{Building a list of companies to reach out to for partnerships}
\li{Identifying target accounts for sales outreach}
\li{Researching companies that match your ideal customer profile}
\li{Preparing for business development activities}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{What This Skill Does}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Understands Your Business}: Analyzes your product/service, value proposition, and target market}
\li{\strong{Identifies Target Companies}: Finds companies that match your ideal customer profile based on:}
\li{Industry and sector}
\li{Company size and location}
\li{Technology stack and tools they use}
\li{Growth stage and funding}
\li{Pain points your product solves}
\li{\strong{Prioritizes Leads}: Ranks companies based on fit score and relevance}
\li{\strong{Provides Contact Strategies}: Suggests how to approach each lead with personalized messaging}
\li{\strong{Enriches Data}: Gathers relevant information about decision-makers and company context}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{How to Use}
\subtree{
\title{Basic Usage}
\p{Simply describe your product/service and what you're looking for:}

\pre{\startverb
I'm building [product description]. Find me 10 companies in [location/industry] 
that would be good leads for this.
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{With Your Codebase}
\p{For even better results, run this from your product's source code directory:}

\pre{\startverb
Look at what I'm building in this repository and identify the top 10 companies 
in [location/industry] that would benefit from this product.
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Advanced Usage}
\p{For more targeted research:}

\pre{\startverb
My product: [description]
Ideal customer profile:
- Industry: [industry]
- Company size: [size range]
- Location: [location]
- Current pain points: [pain points]
- Technologies they use: [tech stack]

Find me 20 qualified leads with contact strategies for each.
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Instructions}
\p{When a user requests lead research:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Understand the Product/Service}}
\li{If in a code directory, analyze the codebase to understand the product}
\li{Ask clarifying questions about the value proposition}
\li{Identify key features and benefits}
\li{Understand what problems it solves}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Define Ideal Customer Profile}}
\li{Determine target industries and sectors}
\li{Identify company size ranges}
\li{Consider geographic preferences}
\li{Understand relevant pain points}
\li{Note any technology requirements}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Research and Identify Leads}}
\li{Search for companies matching the criteria}
\li{Look for signals of need (job postings, tech stack, recent news)}
\li{Consider growth indicators (funding, expansion, hiring)}
\li{Identify companies with complementary products/services}
\li{Check for budget indicators}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Prioritize and Score}}
\li{Create a fit score (1-10) for each lead}
\li{Consider factors like:}
\li{Alignment with ICP}
\li{Signals of immediate need}
\li{Budget availability}
\li{Competitive landscape}
\li{Timing indicators}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Provide Actionable Output}}
\li{\strong{Company Name} and website}
\li{\strong{Why They're a Good Fit}: Specific reasons based on their business}
\li{\strong{Priority Score}: 1-10 with explanation}
\li{\strong{Decision Maker}: Role/title to target (e.g., "VP of Engineering")}
\li{\strong{Contact Strategy}: Personalized approach suggestions}
\li{\strong{Value Proposition}: How your product solves their specific problem}
\li{\strong{Conversation Starters}: Specific points to mention in outreach}
\li{\strong{LinkedIn URL}: If available, for easy connection}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Format the Output}}
}

\p{Present results in a clear, scannable format:}

\pre{\startverb
   # Lead Research Results
   
   ## Summary
   - Total leads found: [X]
   - High priority (8-10): [X]
   - Medium priority (5-7): [X]
   - Average fit score: [X]
   
   ---
   
   ## Lead 1: [Company Name]
   
   **Website**: [URL]
   **Priority Score**: [X/10]
   **Industry**: [Industry]
   **Size**: [Employee count/revenue range]
   
   **Why They're a Good Fit**:
   [2-3 specific reasons based on their business]
   
   **Target Decision Maker**: [Role/Title]
   **LinkedIn**: [URL if available]
   
   **Value Proposition for Them**:
   [Specific benefit for this company]
   
   **Outreach Strategy**:
   [Personalized approach - mention specific pain points, recent company news, or relevant context]
   
   **Conversation Starters**:
   - [Specific point 1]
   - [Specific point 2]
   
   ---
   
   [Repeat for each lead]
\stopverb}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Offer Next Steps}}
\li{Suggest saving results to a CSV for CRM import}
\li{Offer to draft personalized outreach messages}
\li{Recommend prioritization based on timing}
\li{Suggest follow-up research for top leads}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Examples}
\subtree{
\title{Example 1: From Lenny's Newsletter}
\p{\strong{User}: "I'm building a tool that masks sensitive data in AI coding assistant queries. Find potential leads."}

\p{\strong{Output}: Creates a prioritized list of companies that:}

\ul{
\li{Use AI coding assistants (Copilot, Cursor, etc.)}
\li{Handle sensitive data (fintech, healthcare, legal)}
\li{Have evidence in their GitHub repos of using coding agents}
\li{May have accidentally exposed sensitive data in code}
\li{Includes LinkedIn URLs of relevant decision-makers}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example 2: Local Business}
\p{\strong{User}: "I run a consulting practice for remote team productivity. Find me 10 companies in the Bay Area that recently went remote."}

\p{\strong{Output}: Identifies companies that:}

\ul{
\li{Recently posted remote job listings}
\li{Announced remote-first policies}
\li{Are hiring distributed teams}
\li{Show signs of remote work challenges}
\li{Provides personalized outreach strategies for each}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Tips for Best Results}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Be specific} about your product and its unique value}
\li{\strong{Run from your codebase} if applicable for automatic context}
\li{\strong{Provide context} about your ideal customer profile}
\li{\strong{Specify constraints} like industry, location, or company size}
\li{\strong{Request follow-up} research on promising leads for deeper insights}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Related Use Cases}
\ul{
\li{Drafting personalized outreach emails after identifying leads}
\li{Building a CRM-ready CSV of qualified prospects}
\li{Researching specific companies in detail}
\li{Analyzing competitor customer bases}
\li{Identifying partnership opportunities}
}
}
}